pullRequest.body:
In this PR, we continue to port a part of Andrew Yang's lean3 repository at [this repository](https://github.com/erdOne/lean-AG-morphisms), which is appoved by @erdOne after his discussion with @chrisflav . This PR follows #20741 (merged by Bors) and #20744.

We ported Andrew's definition of `Ideal.height` and `Ideal.primeHeight` with some small changes in #20741, and in this PR, we ported some more lemmas about these definitions, finishing the porting work of dimension_theory/height.lean in that repository.

- [ ] depends on: #20744 [some of the lemmas used spanRank]
Co-authored-by:
@erdOne
@Xuchun-Li [li.xuchun@qq.com](mailto:li.xuchun@qq.com)
@jjdishere [emailboxofjjd@163.com](mailto:emailboxofjjd@163.com)
@Blackfeather007 [2100017455@stu.pku.edu.cn](mailto:2100017455@stu.pku.edu.cn)
@ShouxinZhang [202013140018@nuist.edu.cn](mailto:202013140018@nuist.edu.cn)

<!-- By Dependent Issues (Action) - DO NOT REMOVE -->
This should just be an abbrev of `FiniteDimensionalOrder (PrimeSpectrum R)`. And the lemmas should be added for arbitrary orders (and I'm guessing most of them already exists)
This has nothing to do with localization and can probably live in `Basic.lean`

```suggestion
    (J.map (algebraMap R A)).minimalPrimes = Ideal.comap (algebraMap R A) ⁻¹' J.minimalPrimes := by
```

pullRequest.title: feat(RingTheory/Ideal): more lemmas about the height of an ideal
